<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code> element embeds audio content with native browser playback controls. Vanilla Breeze styles audio players to be block-level and full-width by default, with variants for compact and minimal layouts.</p>
    <p>Audio handling follows a progressive enhancement approach with four layers — each functional on its own:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Layer 1</strong> — Native <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code> with <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> fallback chain</li>
      <li><strong>Layer 2</strong> — CSS styling: <code>accent-color</code>, <code>border-radius</code>, <code>color-scheme</code></li>
      <li><strong>Layer 3</strong> — Track listing via <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> + <code>&lt;ol class="track-list"&gt;</code></li>
      <li><strong>Layer 4</strong> — <a href="/docs/elements/web-components/audio-player/"><code>&lt;audio-player&gt;</code></a> web component with custom controls</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Podcasts</strong> — Episode players with playback controls</li>
      <li><strong>Music players</strong> — Song or album playback</li>
      <li><strong>Sound effects</strong> — UI feedback or game audio</li>
      <li><strong>Voice recordings</strong> — Interviews, voicemail, audio messages</li>
      <li><strong>Audiobooks</strong> — Narrated content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Layer 1: Native Baseline</h2>
    <p>Works everywhere with no CSS or JS. Always include at least one <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> with a <code>type</code> attribute and a download link as the ultimate fallback.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <audio controls>
        <source src="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
        <p>Your browser does not support audio. <a href="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" download>Download the audio file</a>.</p>
      </audio>
    </div>
    <code-block language="html" label="Basic audio with fallback download link">{{ basicAudioCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Multi-Source Format Chain</h3>
    <p>List formats best-to-worst — the browser picks the first it supports.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Full format fallback chain">{{ multiSourceCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Layer 2: Styled Variants</h2>
    <p>CSS-only improvements via VB tokens. The native player gains visual polish without any new HTML.</p>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <p>Full-width player with <code>accent-color</code>, <code>border-radius</code>, and <code>color-scheme</code> from VB tokens.</p>
    <div class="example">
      <audio controls>
        <source src="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
      </audio>
    </div>

    <h3>.compact</h3>
    <p>Max-width constrained (320px) for inline usage or sidebars.</p>
    <div class="example">
      <audio class="compact" controls>
        <source src="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
      </audio>
    </div>
    <code-block language="html" label="Compact audio player">{{ compactAudioCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.minimal</h3>
    <p>Reduced height for tight layouts.</p>
    <div class="example">
      <audio class="minimal" controls>
        <source src="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
      </audio>
    </div>
    <code-block language="html" label="Minimal audio player">{{ minimalAudioCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Layer 3: Track Listing</h2>
    <p>HTML + CSS only. <code>&lt;details&gt;/&lt;summary&gt;</code> exposes a track list that shows and hides natively. Without JS, track links navigate to the audio file. With the playlist utility loaded, clicking a track updates the audio source and plays it.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <section class="audio-standalone">
        <audio controls>
          <source src="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
          <p><a href="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3" download>Download track 1</a></p>
        </audio>
        <details open>
          <summary>Track Listing</summary>
          <ol class="track-list">
            <li data-audio-active>
              <a href="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3">01. Opening Theme</a>
              <span class="track-meta"><time datetime="PT2M14S">2:14</time></span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3">02. Main Theme</a>
              <span class="track-meta"><time datetime="PT3M45S">3:45</time></span>
            </li>
            <li data-audio-favorite>
              <a href="/docs/examples/demos/assets/track.mp3">03. Battle Theme</a>
              <span class="track-meta"><time datetime="PT1M58S">1:58</time></span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </details>
      </section>
    </div>
    <code-block language="html" label="Audio with track listing (CSS-only structure)">{{ trackListCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Interactive Playlist (with JS)</h3>
    <p>Wrap the audio and track list in a container with class <code>.audio-standalone</code> to enable click-to-play behavior via the playlist utility.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Standalone interactive playlist">{{ standalonePlaylistCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Track List Data Attributes</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Set by</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>data-audio-active</code></td><td>Component + author</td><td>Currently loaded/playing track</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-audio-played</code></td><td>Component</td><td>Track has been played this session</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-audio-favorite</code></td><td>Author</td><td>Editorially marked as a highlight</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Text Tracks</h2>

    <h3>Captions</h3>
    <code-block language="html" label="Audio with captions track">{{ captionsCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Chapters</h3>
    <code-block language="html" label="Audio with chapter markers">{{ chaptersCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Audio Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>controls</code></td>
          <td>Show native playback controls (required for user interaction)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>autoplay</code></td>
          <td>Start playing automatically (discouraged — poor UX)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>muted</code></td>
          <td>Start with audio muted</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>loop</code></td>
          <td>Restart audio when it ends</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>preload</code></td>
          <td><code>none</code>, <code>metadata</code>, or <code>auto</code></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Preload Options</h3>
    <code-block language="html" label="Audio preload attribute options">{{ preloadOptionsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Audio Formats</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Format</th><th>MIME Type</th><th>Support</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>MP3</td><td><code>audio/mpeg</code></td><td>Universal — best for compatibility</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AAC</td><td><code>audio/aac</code></td><td>Good quality, wide support</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ogg Vorbis</td><td><code>audio/ogg</code></td><td>Open format, Firefox/Chrome</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Opus</td><td><code>audio/opus</code></td><td>Best quality/size ratio, modern browsers</td></tr>
        <tr><td>WAV</td><td><code>audio/wav</code></td><td>Uncompressed, large files</td></tr>
        <tr><td>FLAC</td><td><code>audio/flac</code></td><td>Lossless, growing support</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Transcripts</h3>
    <p>Provide text transcripts for audio content so deaf users and those who cannot play audio can access the information.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Audio with transcript link for accessibility">{{ transcriptCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Always provide a text transcript for important audio</li>
      <li>Never autoplay audio — it is disruptive and inaccessible</li>
      <li>Ensure controls are visible and keyboard accessible</li>
      <li>Provide context about what the audio contains</li>
      <li>Include duration information when available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <p>Styles defined in <code>/src/native-elements/audio/styles.css</code></p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Selector</th><th>Properties</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>audio</code></td>
          <td><code>display: block; width: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-m); accent-color: var(--color-primary); color-scheme: light dark;</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>audio.compact</code></td>
          <td><code>max-width: 320px;</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
